Operations.Description:
Lists records for the specified custom object by searching against record identifiers and field values.

Sample request for search by fields

POST /search

{
  "fieldValueSearchFilters": [
   {
     "fieldName": "MyDecimalField",
     "operation": ">",
     "operand": 10
   },
   {
     "fieldName": "MyTextField",
     "operation": "startsWith",
     "operand": "Field Val"
   }
 ]
}


Sample request for search by ids

POST /search

{
  "ids": [
    "d8d9a288-c0b9-4aed-b3dc-e0d521329ce6",
    "36782adb-54d6-4cef-ae90-455585b66dcf",
    "61dcce88-0281-468b-8589-7690105f3916"
  ]
}


Sample request for search by record identities

POST /search

{
  "recordIdentifiers": [
     1,
     5,
     10
  ]
}


Sample request for search by system fields To search by a system field (such as modifiedDateTime), use a leading underscore with the field name.

POST /search

{
  "fieldValueSearchFilters": [
   {
     "fieldName": "_modifiedDateTime",
     "operation": ">",
     "operand": "2015-03-14T09:26:53.59Z"
   }
 ]
}

